ml plus src through public git commands, initialize rebar, create exactly one task via JSON CLI output, and claim it once through the public atomic claim command. Visible happy path GREEN: 2 passed. Focused Ruff check and format-check GREEN. Static fixtures, production code, and oracle assertions untouched by implementation.","timestamp":1784869453281236001},{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Held-out remediation validated. Independent strong-tier implementer completed fixture-only support in 2 substantive attempts. Restored full oracle: 4/4 GREEN across Python/TypeScript and analyzer-present/absent. Defect-seeded mutations proved teeth: empty commit produced churn 0 vs expected 8/10 (2/2 RED); omitting claim produced empty attempts map vs [1] (2/2 RED); restored 4/4 GREEN. Focused metrics: 102 passed, 2 skipped. make lint GREEN; make typecheck GREEN; make test GREEN: 7124 passed, 29 skipped, 114 deselected.","timestamp":1784871770317718001}],"created_at":1784517475532064001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"72274f89-396b-41d3-a952-62b7ac599799","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"0734-ceae-be55-4fa7"},{"link_uuid":"8151981b-3e22-4845-8213-18d628358dc6","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"c23c-c32b-982c-4196"}],"description":"## Description\nProve portability end-to-end: run the code_health lens against a Python client fixture AND a non-Python client fixture (Go or TS), asserting real values when analyzers are present and honest Unavailable when the `[metrics]` extra / external tools are absent. Epic headline AC.\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- Specify HOW the real tools become available: mark the \"present\" assertions as INTEGRATION tests gated on tool availability (skip-if-absent for scc/jscpd/npx; lizard via the `[metrics]` extra), so CI without the tools still passes and a tool-provisioned run exercises the real path.\n- Dependency text corrected to the recorded edge (depends_on 0734); adapters 18f9/21fb/3ba0 are covered transitively through 0734.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Fixtures: one Python, one non-Python (Go or TS), each with a minimal rebar ticket-store shape.\n- [ ] Analyzers present (integration, skip-if-absent): code_health computes for BOTH languages.\n- [ ] Extra/tools absent (always-run): code_health reports Unavailable for both — no crash, no fabricated data.\n- [ ] agent_process + git-delta metrics compute for both.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Interface/E2E test covering both fixtures and both present/absent states.\n\n## Dependencies: 0734 (recorded edge); transitively 18f9/21fb/3ba0.\n## Files likely touched: tests/interfaces/test_metrics_polyglot.py (new), tests/fixtures/metrics_polyglot/ (new)\n## Estimated scope: M","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"tests/interfaces/test_metrics_polyglot.py","reason":"new: Python + non-Python fixtures; analyzers present -> values; absent -> Unavailable"},{"path":"tests/fixtures/metrics_polyglot/","reason":"new: minimal Python and Go/TS client fixtures"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","0734-ceae-be55-4fa7"],["depends_on","c23c-c32b-982c-4196"],["parent","839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051"]],"parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","parent_status_uuid":"97cb1288-9cdd-403c-9888-61e4093435cc","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_id":"a532-4e67-562c-4893","ticket_type":"story","title":"Cross-language validation: code_health on a Python and a non-Python client project","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["dc718833-bd10-4a8a-8f54-11a144c29dca","72274f89-396b-41d3-a952-62b7ac599799","238a0f2f-9ba2-4a4f-9138-7046fe488914","473e600b-ae9f-4e46-b6b7-94a960cd7b2b","dffd5b1a-19dc-45a4-9199-1f1c62908a7c","8151981b-3e22-4845-8213-18d628358dc6","97cb1288-9cdd-4